<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">The Federal Council</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fogg</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Not having yet up to this time received answer to the note which it had
                            the honor to address the 3d July, 1883, to the minister resident of the
                            United States of America, concerning contributions in favor of the
                            family of Jean Zweifel, the federal council thinks it ought to remind
                            Mr. George G. Fogg of this affair, and seizes this occasion to renew to
                            him the assurances, &amp;c., &amp;c.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>DR. J. DUBS.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>